currentDoc:
What Stereotypical Characters Make You Cringe?

What stereotypical characters in books, movies or television shows make you cringe and why? Would you ever not watch or read something because of its offensive portrayal of someone?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: My personal pet peeve is when people (writers or showrunners) portray a character with a disability and it is offensive.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: My personal pet peeve is when people (writers or showrunners) portray a character with a disability and it is offensive.

currentSuggestions.original: Especially if they're about someone of a particular race, ethnic group, religion -- especially, of course, if it's a negative stereotype.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Especially if they're about someone of a particular race, ethnic group, religion -- especially, of course, if it's a negative stereotype.

currentSuggestions.original: I'm not a huge fan of the Harry Potter series, and it's because I don't like how I can predict exactly what sort of person Hermione
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I'm not a huge fan of the Harry Potter series, and it's because I don't like how I can predict exactly what sort of person Hermione

currentSuggestions.original: I cringe every time I hear someone say anything about "Southerners" or "Yankees."
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I cringe every time I hear someone say anything about "Southerners" or "Yankees."

currentSuggestions.original: Most of the time, they are very offensive.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Most of the time, they are very offensive.

currentSuggestions.original: The portrayal was not funny, realistic or funny at all.
